cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as aspect-based sentiment analysis. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a multi-task learning network for joint learning of related tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a neural network model for NLP tasks. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment analysis is often used in information retrieval systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for multi-task learning.
